Enter our revolutionary solution – a GEN AI-driven support system that transforms how we handle alerts.

🔍 The Journey of the Alert
The Alert Arrives:
When Wormly sends an alert, our intelligent Alert Ingestion & Validation Agent kicks into gear.

It swiftly checks the alert's details, including error types and affected services.
Using advanced observability tools like Prometheus and Datadog, it verifies whether the alert is true or false.
True Alert Scenario:
If the alert is confirmed as true, here’s where the magic happens:

The GenAI Diagnostic & Analysis Agent springs into action. It gathers logs, traces, and historical incident data to analyze the root cause.
In seconds, it prepares a concise incident summary with actionable insights for the support team.
Simultaneously, the system auto-generates notifications via Slack or Microsoft Teams, sharing the analysis and suggested remediation steps with the engineers.
False Alert Scenario:
Now, if the alert is deemed false:

The system doesn’t just sit idle. Instead, it captures the website’s current state by taking screenshots and collecting console logs using tools like Puppeteer.
It then analyzes these logs for anomalies, missing elements, or any failed network requests, providing a comprehensive diagnostic report.
All findings are automatically logged in JIRA, helping to refine monitoring rules and reduce future false alarms.
🎯 The Impact of Our Solution
Speed: Alerts are validated in real-time, significantly reducing response times.
Accuracy: By filtering out false alarms, our system minimizes unnecessary disruptions.
Empowerment: Engineers receive crucial insights without the burden of manual checks, allowing them to focus on solving the real issues.
🌟 The Transformation
Thanks to this GEN AI-driven architecture, support teams no longer scramble in confusion. Instead, they’re empowered with actionable insights, reducing stress and enabling a proactive approach to incident management.

"Now, instead of worrying about false alarms, engineers can trust the system to guide them, freeing up their time to innovate and improve our services
